  "prompt": "What can I do with an expired passport?",
  "response": "An expired passport can still be useful in several ways:\n\n1. **Identification Purposes**: In some situations, an expired passport can still be used as a form of identification. For example, it may suffice for certain types of administrative paperwork or for proving your identity in non-governmental contexts.\n\n2. **Renewal**: You can use it to renew your passport. The expired passport will serve as an important reference and prove your previous citizenship status.\n\n3. **Travel to Certain Countries**: Some countries allow entry with recently expired passports, but restrictions vary. Always check entry requirements before travel.\n\n4. **Memorabilia**: You can keep it as a personal souvenir of your travels. It holds sentimental value and memories of places visited.\n\n5. **Proof of Nationality**: It can still serve as proof of nationality, which may be needed in various situations, like applying for a visa or citizenship documents.\n\n6. **Historical Record**: It can be beneficial for tracing family history, research purposes, or personal documentation.\n\nRemember, the rules and regulations regarding expired passports may vary by country and specific context. Always verify with relevant authorities or consult official sources for the most accurate information.",
